  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, what happened was the system was this way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At some point, we went through-- at Fort Benjamin Harrison-- we took all those basic examinations.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We took the examinations-- the academic kinds, and the psychological examinations.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All those occurred at Fort Benjamin Harrison.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When they got through with those, now in retrospect I know that they would-- they use those examinations and our background and experiences, whatever we were, to make a judgment about what-- what branch of the service they would send you to.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And also to what camp they would send you to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what happened was they talked about-- to me about being a draftsman, 'cause I was in engineering school, and I had taken drafting and things of the sort.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- finally, one day they called us all out and they had trains all over the place and they told us to pack our bags.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we came out, and at that point, they gave each one of us a-- a number.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the number related to a train, and when they got through, all of us was on a train going somewhere.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we happened to be going to-- the group I was with was all going to Camp Lee, Virginia, which was down outside of Richmond in Petersburg, Virginia.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And now they put us on trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And what happened was the train-- they told us later-- I was talking to one of the people who ran-- one of the conductors.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said they were taking us over a lot of unused tracks so they wouldn't bog down the commercial traffic.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went all the way down from-- from Fort Benjamin Harrison across Cincinnati.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in Cincinnati the guy told us, now, they're, all loaded, the black soldiers, up in the front cars.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
